@node FILES "Archive contents & PGP info"
ARCHIVE CONTENTS & PGP INFO
---------------------------

The complete, unregistered program consists of the following files (and
*only* these files!)

    PayAdvice               (the PayAdvice program)
    PayAdvice.sig           (PGP signature for PayAdvice)
    PayAdvice.info          (program icon)
    PayAdvice.Guide         (the instructions - you're reading them!)
    PayAdvice.Guide.info    (instructions icon)
    PayAdvice.Readme        (brief summary about the program)
    PayAdvice.Readme.info   (readme icon)
    reqtools.library        (required library)

If you've got access to PGP, then make sure that you use the PGP signature
to check the integrity of PayAdvice *before* using the program. My public
PGP key is below - you'll find my PGP key fingerprint in my on-line resume
on CIX, or just drop me a line and ask for it.

To actually check the integrity of the PayAdvice executable, all you have
to do is add my public key to your PGP keyring and then type the following
in a Shell window...

    PGP PayAdvice.sig PayAdvice

...and a message will be displayed telling you whether or not it's safe to
use this copy of the program.

Here is my public PGP key:

